            <div type="edition" subtype="transcription" ana="b1">
                <p>
               <g type="palm-branch"/>
               <lb/>Μνημῖον<lb/>
               <g type="cross"/>Κυριακὴ Σ<supplied reason="omitted">εά</supplied>
               <g type="cross"/>
               <lb break="no"/>
               <supplied reason="omitted">λ</supplied>ου, ἀ<supplied reason="omitted">π</supplied>ο<supplied reason="omitted">θ</supplied>ανο<supplied reason="omitted">ῦ</supplied>
               <lb break="no"/>σαν μετὰ κα<lb break="no"/>
               <supplied reason="omitted">λ</supplied>οῦ ὀνόματο<supplied reason="omitted">ς</supplied>
               <lb/>καὶ κ<supplied reason="omitted">αλ</supplied>ῆς <supplied reason="omitted">π</supplied>ίσ<lb break="no"/>τεως ἐτῶν <num value="17">ιζ</num>
               <lb/>ἐ<supplied reason="omitted">ν</supplied> ἔτους <num value="329">τκ<supplied reason="omitted">θ</supplied>
               </num>.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" ana="b1">
                <p>Monument of Kyriake, daughter of Seal(l)os, who died having a good name and good
                    faith at the age of 17 years, in the year 329.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" ana="b1">
                <p>The numerous vulgarisms indicate that this tombstone is not authentic and was
                    produced by an engraver ignorant of Greek. The transcription provided has been
                    edited by the original authors using the original epitaph to correct the
                    numerous mistakes in the copy.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
